				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Very good tactics in the above post. Just wanted to put in my 2 cents. I havent gotten to level 29 with my shaman yet but I can tell you the tactics i used with an enchanter. I would get quite aways away from a blue white or sometimes yellow creature and make sure their was another close. then cast tashan on the creature and as it was running toward me i would hit it with charm 9 times out of ten even a yellow mob would become charmed then immediately send it to kill another same level to it then i would weakin the other mob a little and sit and med keeping an eye on both creatures hp's while i med. when the creature was lo on hps i would nuke it and kill it then sit the charmed one down and get a long ways from it and med it would normally be very hurt so if it came uncharmed i would kill it or mez it and get clear of it. This is a little more aggressive aproach yet alot more risky to. dont know how it will work with a shaman becuse we dont have the spells an enchanter has anyway food for thought looking forward to level 29. 
				</font>
